Txt_Talk_SwampCave_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0120_0.Text:
*: Dig ye, dig ye! Dig, dig, dig!
Dig, and dig yet more!

Txt_Talk_SwampCave_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0110_0.Text: *: ...What say'st thou? Thou gavest the Lord of the Underworld a drubbing? Zounds, thou art mighty indeed!

Txt_Talk_SwampCave_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0220_0.Text: *: We dig here a tunnel, that others might pass more freely through this land.

Txt_Talk_SwampCave_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0210_0.Text: *: What sayest thou? The morn hath finally come to the lands above?
*: If this be true, then verily, we must make haste! Dig, my boys! Dig ye for all that you are worth!

Txt_Talk_SwampCave_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0320_0.Text: *: Dig ye, dig ye! Dig, that we might reach Rimuldar ere this moon is out!

Txt_Talk_SwampCave_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0410_0.Text: *: Quickly! That we might bathe in the sun's rays all the sooner! Hup! Hoy!

Txt_Talk_SwampCave_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0510_0.Text: *: Heh... Look at all these fine specimens.
...and a monster is revealed before your eyes!
Seems I'm in for a spot of toil and trouble...
{LEADER} calms the monster with a soothing voice and tells it about Monty's monster menagerie...

Txt_Talk_SwampCave_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0620_0.Text: *: Just a minute<--->I've seen that mug before! Fancy bumpin' into you in this of all places.
*: As you can see I'm not exactly livin' the 'igh life lately. Makes me miss the good old days when I got to go on adventures with the boss.
*: Come to fink of it, there was one last place we was 'opin' to pay a visit before we wound up 'ere.
*: Was this odd spot called Gaia's Navel.
*: I remember the boss once sayin' that merchants 'ave no business dealin' in fancy metals and ores.
*: Said somefink about only trustin' smiths an' dwarves to work with 'em.

Txt_Talk_SwampCave_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0610_0.Text: *: 'Ello, mate! Got the day off today fanks to Zoma apparently givin' up the ghost.
*: Don't believe it for one second meself, but I ain't complainin'!

Txt_Talk_SwampCave_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0720_0.Text: *: Oof, me back and shoulders ain't up to this... Wish I could just go back to stealin' fings...
*: If I could just get me 'ands on that bleedin' blue rock I've 'eard so much about... I'd be set for life.
*: Wot? You ain't 'eard of it? It's got this funny old name... Zenithium, that's it!
*: Nightmare to get yer 'ands on though. They say you'd need a bomb big enuff to blow an 'ole in a wall as fick as the boss.
*: Heh, no clue why, but I just suddenly remembered this funny dwarf I met a while ago.
*: 'E was a real stubborn fella, let me tell ya. They're not all like that, though. I've met one that was pretty friendly too.
*: Wassat? Oh, the nice one? I fink I met 'im in this little 'ut way north o' Mur. There was plenty of snow 'bout the place and it was somewhere near the sea.

Txt_Talk_SwampCave_1F_SUB_0_ACTOR_0710_0.Text: *: Did ya 'ear? Zoma's popped 'is clogs! Mad, innit? And that's not all: I've been given the day off too! The Goddess is finally smilin' on me...
*: No clue who did the rotter in, but I'm pleased as punch! Cheers to 'em, whoever it was!
